	<p>
	<br>
	But me and my friend decided to sell it any way in open market than letting them rot. We hand plucked and cleaned nearly 100 kg of cucumber and rushed to the Sunday "chanda" -bidding place for farm products. We saw a lot of farmers flocking the place to get thier vegetables sold. All the items were bought by local shopkeepers at a very cheap price.Occasionally few got better prices due to shortage of that particular product and there was a demand for it.We had to sell our cucumber for 3 Rs per Kg and that too only 50 Kg were sold. Nobody was there to buy the rest 50 Kg as we were told it was" too ripened". 
	<br>
	The "Novice farmer" ego was hurt badly and more importantly we learned quite few important lessons.
