	I came back from native and my mind was uneasy with all that happened. It was not our products were too ripened, but many others had to settle to any price that was given as it was nearly impossible for them to take back farm products to home if prices were unsatisfactory and these are perishables and had to be sold anyway before they rot. I felt farmers are gambling a tough game every single day than a stock market dealer. I think there is large gap between the farmers -market and middle men are taking a lot of advantages leaving farmers in peril.
	<br>
	We are thinking of bringing some change to this. We were thinking of  having an online marketplace where people can register their products and sell it. Let me know your views on it.
	This is not a new concept, but there are so many e-commerce site to sell lifestyle products but not many or zero in many places to sell the Essentials. It is a place where we want to put our stake and this is a basic survey to know the pulse of the people who actually are doing farming. We ask why life supporting farmers be in misery when life styling products have glamorous reception. (we don't oppose them, but want to stress the point).
